
[1]correctness

   CORRECTNESS, n.

   1. Conformity to truth, justice, or propriety; as the correctness of
   opinions, of judgment, or of manners.

   2. Conformity to settled usages or rules; as correctness in writing or
   speaking.

   3. Conformity to a copy or original; as the correctness of a book.

   4. Conformity to established rules of taste or proportion; as the
   correctness of design in painting, sculpture or architecture.
